Etymology.
The specific epithet is an adjective referring to variable (
versi
) colour (
color
) of the species in life.

Colouration in life (
Fig. 2
): Background colour yellowish, especially the head which is almost pale yellow, upper parts of trunk and tail with bright orange tinge, underparts light yellowish. A series of lateral dorsal scales on the trunk with a dark basal spot forming broken bands across the trunk at fairly regular intervals. Limbs in a shade of brown with randomly placed dark brown to black spots.

